Definition: a graphic or vivid verbal description
Example: too often the narrative was interrupted by long word pictures; the author gives a depressing picture of life in Poland; the pamphlet contained brief characterizations of famous Vermonters
Synonyms: word-painting, delineation, verb, stative, delineate, communication, depiction, depict, picture, characterization, characterisation, characterise, description, a, graphic, or, vivid, verbal, too, often, the, narrative, was, interrupted, by, long, word, pictures, author, gives, depressing, of, life, in, Poland, pamphlet, contained, brief, characterizations, famous, Vermonters
Category: noun.communication
